    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="546"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/28440: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-11T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 11, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>585. Foreign Office assures me Franco<note n="10" xml:id="d546fn10">Gen.
                        Francisco Franco, Spanish Chief of State.</note> has told Germans not only
                    that he will resist aggression from any side but that Spain will not even
                    discuss possible military concessions to the Axis.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Algiers for Murphy<note n="11" xml:id="d546fn11">Robert D. Murphy,
                        Chief Civil Affairs Officer at Algiers; U.S. Political Adviser, staff of the
                        Supreme Allied Commander, Mediterranean Theater; Personal Representative of
                        President Roosevelt in North Africa, with the rank of Minister.</note> and
                    Lisbon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
